<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-58-0379 </DOCNO><TEXT>Radionuclide scanning of the peritoneal cavity is not frequently performedin most nuclear medicine departments, but it can play a significant rolein the diagnosis and treatment of suspected intra-abdominal abscesses,as well as in the evaluation of possibly malfunctioning intraperitonealshunts. Several techniques have been described and are discussed alongwith potential sources of error in diagnosis. The therapeutic use ofradionuclides in the peritoneal cavity has been in existence for over30 years, most commonly in the treatment of malignant ascites and micrometastasesdue to ovarian carcinoma. This is also be briefly reviewed.</TEXT></DOC>